+{"id":"jeffreysprompts.com-3fms","title":"Add visual separation between Featured and Browse sections","description":"# Task: Clarify Featured vs Browse Section Boundary

## Problem Statement
Currently, the Featured section appears immediately after the Hero, followed by the filter controls and browse grid. This creates confusion because:

1. **Filters don't affect featured**: User applies a filter, sees 6 featured prompts unchanged, thinks filtering is broken
2. **No visual boundary**: Featured and Browse blend together
3. **Duplicated prompts**: Featured prompts may appear again in the browse grid

## Current Layout
```
Hero (search + category pills)
    ↓
Featured Prompts (6 cards, unaffected by filters)
    ↓
Filter Controls (Category, Tags, Clear)
    ↓
Results Header ("All Prompts" / "Search Results")
    ↓
Browse Grid (filtered results)
```

## Proposed Solution

### Option A: Move Featured Above Filters, Add Clear Separator
```tsx
{/* Hero */}
<Hero ... />

{/* Featured Section - clearly labeled, visually distinct */}
<section className="py-8 border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
  <div className="container-wide">
    <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
      <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold flex items-center gap-2">
        <Sparkles className="w-5 h-5 text-amber-500" />
        Featured Prompts
      </h2>
      <span className="text-sm text-neutral-500">
        Curated by the team
      </span>
    </div>
    <FeaturedPromptsSection ... />
  </div>
</section>

{/* Clear visual break */}
<div className="h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-neutral-200 dark:via-neutral-800 to-transparent" />

{/* Browse Section - with filters */}
<section className="py-8">
  <div className="container-wide">
    <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">Browse All Prompts</h2>
    <FilterControls ... />
    <PromptGrid ... />
  </div>
</section>
```

### Option B: Integrate Featured into Results
Remove separate featured section. Instead:
- Add "Featured" badge to featured prompts in the grid
- Sort featured prompts to top by default
- Filters affect all prompts including featured

```tsx
// In PromptGrid or page.tsx
const sortedPrompts = useMemo(() => {
  // Featured first, then the rest
  const featured = filteredPrompts.filter(p => p.featured);
  const nonFeatured = filteredPrompts.filter(p => !p.featured);
  return [...featured, ...nonFeatured];
}, [filteredPrompts]);
```

### Option C: Collapsible Featured Section (Best of Both)
Show featured by default, allow collapsing:
```tsx
const [showFeatured, setShowFeatured] = useState(true);

<Collapsible open={showFeatured} onOpenChange={setShowFeatured}>
  <CollapsibleTrigger className="flex items-center justify-between w-full py-4">
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <Sparkles className="w-5 h-5 text-amber-500" />
      <span className="font-semibold">Featured Prompts</span>
      <Badge variant="secondary">{featuredCount}</Badge>
    </div>
    <ChevronDown className={cn("w-4 h-4 transition-transform", showFeatured && "rotate-180")} />
  </CollapsibleTrigger>
  <CollapsibleContent>
    <FeaturedPromptsSection ... />
  </CollapsibleContent>
</Collapsible>
```

## Recommended Approach
**Option A** is simplest and clearest:
